communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education. Might affect crew.\n\nCandidate D: strong problem solving, concentration, responsibility, but hot temper, know-it-all, weak leadership, arrogance. Could affect crew.\n\nCandidate A: anticipates danger, sees complex connections, spatial vision, leadership, but show-off, not open to new ideas, maybe less teamwork.\n\nWhich is best? Need to consider tradeoffs. Perhaps Candidate A's technical and anticipatory skills are strong, leadership good, but teamwork issues moderate. Candidate B's teamwork is poor. Candidate C's communication is poor. Candidate D's temperament is poor.\n\nThus A seems relatively balanced: strong technical, good leadership, moderate teamwork issues but not as severe as others? Show-off may be mitigated. Not open to new ideas could affect adaptability, but long-distance flights need adherence to procedures, maybe not big.\n\nThus provisional preference: Candidate A.\n\nWe should note uncertainties: need more info on actual crew feedback, memory issues for B, etc. What would change vote: if someone has strong evidence of B's teamwork or D's temperament being manageable, could shift.\n\nNow produce output."}
