ous situations, sees complex connections (supports proactive decisions).\n- Professional development: unfriendly, unhealthy eating, show\u2011off, not open to new ideas (may limit growth).\n\nCandidate B:\n- Reliability: very conscientious, handles stress well, but pretentious (Agent\u202f2), makes nasty remarks (Agent\u202f2), weak memory for numbers (Agent\u202f2), sometimes adopts wrong tone (original), pretentious (original). So mixed.\n- Technical competence: good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills, but weak numeric memory.\n- Calmness under pressure: handles stress very well.\n- Decision\u2011making: good at assessing weather conditions (decision support), also handles stress.\n- Professional development: very conscientious (positive), but pretentious, wrong tone, nasty remarks, weak memory for numbers \u2013 may hinder growth.\n\nCandidate C:\n- Reliability: puts concern for others above everything (positive), but egocentric, not willing to further education, difficulty communicating ideas (affects reliability?), keeps calm in crisis (calmness), quick correct decisions (decision), understands complicated technology (technical).\n- Technical competence: understands complicated technology, excellent attention skills, quick correct decisions.\n- Calmness under pressure: keeps calm in a crisis.\n- Decision\u2011making: can make correct decisions quickly.\n- Professional development: not very willing to further his education, egocentric, difficulty communicating ideas.\n\nCandidate D:\n- Reliability: takes responsibility seriously, responds to unexpected events adequately, but moody, loner, hot temper, know\u2011it\u2011all (Agent\u202f2), weak leadership (Agent\u202f2).\n- Technical competence: can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well.\n- Calmness under pressure: moody, hot temper (negative), but responds adequately to unexpected events.\n- Decision\u2011making: solves problems extremely well, responds to unexpected events